<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN242-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. ollaiyūr kiḻāṉmakaṉ peruñcāttaṉaik kuṭavāyiṉallātaṉār (kuṭavāyiṟkīrattaṉār) pāṭiyatu.
        ituvumatu – <app><lem wit="#C2 #C3">ollaiyūr</lem><rdg wit="#C8">ollaiyūrk</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#C2 #C3">kiḻārmaka<space quantity="12" unit="character"/></lem><rdg wit="#C8">kiḻāṉmakaṉ peruñcāttaṉaik kuṭavāyi</rdg></app> ṉallātaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN242">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>iḷaiyōr cūṭār vaḷaiyōr koyyār</l>
<l>nalliyāḻ maruppiṉ mella vāṅkip</l>
<l>pāṇaṉ cūṭāṉ pāṭiṉi yaṇiyā</l>
<l>ḷāṇmai tōṉṟa vāṭavark kaṭanta</l>
<l>valvēṟ cāttaṉ māynta piṉṟai</l>
<l>mullaiyum pūttiyō vollaiyūr nāṭṭē</l></lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The young men won’t wear [it]. Those with bangles won’t pluck [it]. (1)</l>
<l>Not bending [it] softly around the neck of [his] good lute (2)</l>
<l>the bard won’t wear [it]. Songstresses won’t adorn themselves [with it]. (3)</l>
<l>After Cāttaṉ with a strong spear disappeared (5)</l>
<l>who overcame men so that [his] manliness appeared (4)</l>
<l>jasmine, would you flower, in the land of Ollaiyūr? (6)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
